<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,587,897]" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,462,587,614]" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bertoloni" authorityYear="1844" box="[461,713,588,614]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Euphorbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="196" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="adenoptera">
<emphasis box="[461,713,588,614]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">Euphorbia adenoptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread weed, occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[1120,1207,588,614]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="196">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, Central America, the Carribean and South America. In the State of São Paulo the species is only known by specimens collected on roadsides.
</paragraph>
